#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NotesCDRecord.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To make an "ISO" image of three files and two directories.

    mkisofs -l -r -v -o cdImage.iso file1.prm file2.prm file3.prm directory1 directory2

To burn a CD.

    cdrecord -v speed=12 dev=2,0,0 -data cdImage.iso

To burn a DVD using an ISO image called dvdImage.iso.

    dvdrecord -dao -v -speed=2 dev=2,0,0 dvdImage.iso

To copy an ISO image from CD to Disk.

    dd if=/dev/hdc of=Redhat3.iso

Or an alternate form.

    dd if=/dev/cdrom of=cdImage.iso

To find out the device number with

    cdrecord  -scanbus
    dvdrecord -scanbus

To mount an "iso" image.

    mount -o loop /opt/cvs/cdImage.iso /mnt/loop
